SIMPLE: mirth
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mirth
<hw>Mirth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mirthe</ets>,
<ets>murthe</ets>, <ets>merthe</ets>, AS. <ets>myr⟦edh⟧</ets>,
<ets>myrg⟦edh⟧</ets>, <ets>merh⟦edh⟧</ets>, <ets>mirh⟦edh⟧</ets>. See
<er>Merry</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Merriment; gayety accompanied with laughter;
jollity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then will I cause to cease . . . from the streets of Jerusalem,
the voice of <qex>mirth</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. vii. 34.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which causes merriment.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Merriment; joyousness; gladness; fun; frolic;
glee; hilarity; festivity; jollity. See <er>Gladness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mirthful</ent>⟦br⟧
